# Cascade Goods — Project Overview

Cascade Goods is a small e-commerce demo storefront built with Vite, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind v4, React Router, and Zustand. There is no backend — all product data lives in `src/data/`. The app is intentionally lightweight so it can be used to demo Cursor capabilities live in front of an audience.

## Directory map

- `src/pages/` — top-level route components (`HomePage`, `ProductsPage`, `ProductDetailPage`, `CartPage`, `AboutPage`).
- `src/components/layout/` — `Header`, `Footer`, `CartDrawer`. Used on every page via `App.tsx`.
- `src/components/products/` — Product-specific UI (`ProductCard`, `ProductGrid`).
- `src/components/ui/` — Generic primitives (`Button`, `Badge`, `Container`, `StarRating`). Add new primitives here, not inside feature folders.
- `src/data/` — Mock data: `products.ts`, `categories.ts`, `reviews.ts`. Helper selectors (e.g. `getFeaturedProducts`) live alongside the data.
- `src/store/` — Zustand stores. `cart.ts` owns cart state and is persisted to localStorage under `cascade-cart`.
- `src/lib/` — Pure utilities and shared types. `types.ts` is the single source of truth for `Product`, `Category`, and `Review`.

## Routing

All routes are declared in `src/App.tsx`. The category filter on `/products` is driven by the `?category=` query parameter so links can deep-link directly into a filtered view (see `Header.tsx` and `Footer.tsx` for examples).
